      <p class="headline">THE GOAL</p>
      <div>
        <h2 class="headline-h2">
          Transform the app into a pillar of the convention experience.
        </h2>
        <hr />
        <p class="headline">What I delivered:</p>
        <h3>More feedback to capture the event in real-time</h3>
        <h3>
          Features to enhance the social aspects of the con (Schedule sharing)
        </h3>
        <h3>
          Better alignment with the website and everything else at con
          (currently an isolated experience)
        </h3>
        <hr />
        <h3>
          a. More feedback to capture the event in real-time to the best of its
          abilities
        </h3>
        <p>Making updates to the home page.</p>
        <hr />
        <h3>Enhancing the social aspects of con</h3>
        <h3>b. Schedule sharing</h3>
        <p>
          People at con, especially newcomers/first-time congoers, do not know
          what to expect from panels/where to go → give them a starting
          point/point of interest as to where they could/should go. (currently,
          people follow friends around/learn about panels through word of
          mouth/friends ****do a survey to back this up**) Lists could be
          curated by online friends, or real-life friends. Can be shared via
          links on social media, or wherever they message.
        </p>
        <hr />
        <h3>Better alignment with website/brand</h3>
        <p>
          tba 1. Same colour coding as website 2. UI updates that are accuate to
          website branding 3. more robust use of mascot (senmei)
        </p>
      </div>
